node.text:
The Aldabra giant tortoise is endemic to the islands of the Aldabra Atoll in the Seychelles. It is one of the largest tortoises in the world. Lifespan is around 120 years, however there’s is a male by the name of Jonathan which hatched in 1832, and is the oldest known living land animal at 189 years of age. Before Johnathan another male by the name of Adwaita held that record at 206 years of age, unfortunately he died in 2006.

🎥 @thereptilezoo
